TITLE: Defining Enum Aliases in Protocol Buffers
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to create enum aliases by assigning the same value to different enum constants using the allow_alias option. Without this option enabled, duplicate values will generate compiler warnings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protocolbuffers.github.io/blob/main/content/programming-guides/proto3.md#2025-04-11_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: proto
CODE:
```
enum EnumAllowingAlias {
  option allow_alias = true;
  EAA_UNSPECIFIED = 0;
  EAA_STARTED = 1;
  EAA_RUNNING = 1;
  EAA_FINISHED = 2;
}

enum EnumNotAllowingAlias {
  ENAA_UNSPECIFIED = 0;
  ENAA_STARTED = 1;
  // ENAA_RUNNING = 1;  // Uncommenting this line will cause a warning message.
  ENAA_FINISHED = 2;
}
```

