TITLE: Size-Limited Task Processing with proto.Size in Go
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using proto.Size to implement size-based filtering of work tasks to protect downstream systems from oversized messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protocolbuffers.github.io/blob/main/content/reference/go/size.md#2025-04-11_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func (*beamFn) ProcessElement(key string, value []byte, emit func(proto.Message)) {
  task := produceWorkTask(value)
  if proto.Size(task) > 500 * 1024 * 1024 {
    // Skip every work task over 500 MB to not overwhelm
    // the brittle downstream system.
    return
  }
  emit(task)
}
```

