TITLE: Incorrect Usage of proto.Size for Message Unmarshaling in Go
DESCRIPTION: Shows an anti-pattern where proto.Size is incorrectly used for unmarshaling a stream of protocol buffer messages, which can fail with non-minimal wire format messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protocolbuffers.github.io/blob/main/content/reference/go/size.md#2025-04-11_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func bytesToSubscriptionList(data []byte) ([]*vpb.EventSubscription, error) {
    subList := []*vpb.EventSubscription{}
    for len(data) > 0 {
        subscription := &vpb.EventSubscription{}
        if err := proto.Unmarshal(data, subscription); err != nil {
            return nil, err
        }
        subList = append(subList, subscription)
        data = data[:len(data)-proto.Size(subscription)]
    }
    return subList, nil
}
```

