TITLE: EBNF Representation of Numeric Literals
DESCRIPTION: Extended Backus-Naur Form (EBNF) syntax defining various numeric literals including decimal, octal, hexadecimal integers and floating-point numbers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protocolbuffers.github.io/blob/main/content/reference/protobuf/textformat-spec.md#2025-04-11_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: ebnf
CODE:
```
dec_lit   = "0"
          | ( dec - "0" ), { dec } ;
float_lit = ".", dec, { dec }, [ exp ]
          | dec_lit, ".", { dec }, [ exp ]
          | dec_lit, exp ;
exp       = ( "E" | "e" ), [ "+" | "-" ], dec, { dec } ;

DEC_INT   = dec_lit
OCT_INT   = "0", oct, { oct } ;
HEX_INT   = "0", ( "X" | "x" ), hex, { hex } ;
FLOAT     = float_lit, [ "F" | "f" ]
          | dec_lit,   ( "F" | "f" ) ;
```

