TITLE: Implementing a Custom Protocol Compiler in C++
DESCRIPTION: Example of creating a custom protocol compiler that includes support for both C++ and a custom output format called 'Foo'. This demonstrates initializing the CommandLineInterface and registering generators.
SOURCE: https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protocolbuffers.github.io/blob/main/content/reference/cpp/api-docs/google.protobuf.compiler.command_line_interface.md#2025-04-11_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C++
CODE:
```
int main(int argc, char* argv[]) {
  google::protobuf::compiler::CommandLineInterface cli;

  // Support generation of C++ source and headers.
  google::protobuf::compiler::cpp::CppGenerator cpp_generator;
  cli.RegisterGenerator("--cpp_out", &cpp_generator,
    "Generate C++ source and header.");

  // Support generation of Foo code.
  FooGenerator foo_generator;
  cli.RegisterGenerator("--foo_out", &foo_generator,
    "Generate Foo file.");

  return cli.Run(argc, argv);
}
```

